<font color="#FF0000">BETTER?</font><br>
<tt>Wed Sep 24 20:59:16 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I started counseling in 1986.  Started feeling better and dropped about 100 lbs. by 1990.  Shot some perfect scores out on the range and got trophies and respect from my fellow competitors.  Funny how my competition scores improved as my self-esteem did.  Talk about control issues.  My competition was shooting handguns out to 200 meters with iron sights at steel silouettes.  Can't be in more control than that! That .44 mag could shoot better than most scoped rifles!  Weighing each bullet, measuring each gram of powder, sizing each case.  Eliminating all possibilities except the jerk behind the trigger.<br><br>
It worked! I was cured! Sleeping good at night. In touch with my emotions.  Sharing and caring and feeling again.  Marked improvement at work and at home.  Tangible results!  Yeah!!  Felt so good that I was going to get a leave from work and help counsel vets at the Center.  Share the wealth!!  Prove that it could be done..<br><br>
Promotion and new job.  Move from SoCal and all my friends, all my support groups, all that I knew.  Moved to the east coast.  Funny, I never noticed it but Virginia looks a lot like the triple canopy of the Central Highlands.  Especially when a monsoon-like thunderstorm comes rolling through.  My counselor told me before I left that he expected me to stumble a couple of times.  But he knew I wouldn't fall.  Took me a while to understand what he meant.<br><br>
Yep, got here, no friends, new job skills, not a lot of support.  Yep, went to the old fall back position.  Impaired sleep, clamping down, all the easy,old habits.  Feel threatened?  Step back to what works.  No coping skills here, pure survival skills.  I saw it coming.  Reached out again for the VA.  A counselor drove 100 miles one way to work with me for 3 hours, one night a week.  It took a while but I got it back.  And now I think I finally understand.  At least I can see it coming and recognize it for what it is.  Now I have the tools (?) to self correct.<br><br>
I am under no illusions that I am cured.  I can just see it and recognize it and deal with it a lot better.  Hell, I don't know if there is a cure. I know that I sure don't allow events or people to press my buttons.  I can now get pissed at someone and not be making plans to &quot;eliminate my problem&quot;.<br><br>
Just take 2 cans of Spam and a loaf of bread and a jar of mayo and call Ed in the morning.
